{
  "id": "diff-eq-ch06-sec02",
  "title": "Transforms of Basic Functions",
  "chapter": 6,
  "section": 2,
  "book": "diff-eq",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "In this section, we systematically derive the Laplace transforms of the \nfunctions most commonly encountered in differential equations: polynomials, \nexponentials, and trigonometric functions."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Power Functions"
    },
    {
      "type": "theorem",
      "id": "theorem-6.1",
      "number": "6.1",
      "title": "Transform of $t^n$",
      "content": "For $n = 0, 1, 2, \\ldots$ and $s > 0$,\n\\[\n\\mathcal{L}\\{t^n\\} = \\frac{n!}{s^{n+1}}\n\\]",
      "label": "Theorem"
    },
    {
      "type": "proof",
      "content": "We proceed by induction. For $n = 0$, we have already shown that \n$\\mathcal{L}\\{1\\} = 1/s$.\n\nFor general $n$, we use integration by parts with $u = t^n$ and $dv = e^{-st}\\,dt$:\n$$\n\\mathcal{L}\\{t^n\\} &= \\int_0^{\\infty} t^n e^{-st}\\,dt \\\\\n&= \\left[-\\frac{t^n e^{-st}}{s}\\right]_0^{\\infty} + \\frac{n}{s}\\int_0^{\\infty} t^{n-1}e^{-st}\\,dt\n$$\nFor $s > 0$, the boundary term vanishes (using L'HĂ´pital's rule repeatedly \nto show $t^n e^{-st} \\to 0$ as $t \\to \\infty$). Therefore:\n\\[\n\\mathcal{L}\\{t^n\\} = \\frac{n}{s}\\mathcal{L}\\{t^{n-1}\\}\n\\]\nBy induction, if $\\mathcal{L}\\{t^{n-1}\\} = (n-1)!/s^n$, then\n\\[\n\\mathcal{L}\\{t^n\\} = \\frac{n}{s} \\cdot \\frac{(n-1)!}{s^n} = \\frac{n!}{s^{n+1}} \\qedhere\n\\]"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "id": "example-6.1",
      "number": "6.1",
      "title": "Transforms of specific powers",
      "problem": "$$\n\\mathcal{L}\\{1\\} &= \\frac{0!}{s^1} = \\frac{1}{s} \\\\[0.5em]\n\\mathcal{L}\\{t\\} &= \\frac{1!}{s^2} = \\frac{1}{s^2} \\\\[0.5em]\n\\mathcal{L}\\{t^2\\} &= \\frac{2!}{s^3} = \\frac{2}{s^3} \\\\[0.5em]\n\\mathcal{L}\\{t^3\\} &= \\frac{3!}{s^4} = \\frac{6}{s^4} \\\\[0.5em]\n\\mathcal{L}\\{t^4\\} &= \\frac{4!}{s^5} = \\frac{24}{s^5}\n$$",
      "solution": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "id": "example-6.2",
      "number": "6.2",
      "title": "Transform of a polynomial",
      "problem": "Find $\\mathcal{L}\\{3t^2 - 5t + 7\\}$.\n\n**Solution.** By linearity:\n$$\n\\mathcal{L}\\{3t^2 - 5t + 7\\} &= 3\\mathcal{L}\\{t^2\\} - 5\\mathcal{L}\\{t\\} + 7\\mathcal{L}\\{1\\} \\\\\n&= 3 \\cdot \\frac{2}{s^3} - 5 \\cdot \\frac{1}{s^2} + 7 \\cdot \\frac{1}{s} \\\\\n&= \\frac{6}{s^3} - \\frac{5}{s^2} + \\frac{7}{s}\n$$",
      "solution": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Exponential Functions"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "We have already established the fundamental result:"
    },
    {
      "type": "theorem",
      "id": "theorem-6.2",
      "number": "6.2",
      "title": "Transform of $e^{at",
      "content": "$}\nFor any real constant $a$ and $s > a$,\n\\[\n\\mathcal{L}\\{e^{at}\\} = \\frac{1}{s-a}\n\\]",
      "label": "Theorem"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "id": "example-6.3",
      "number": "6.3",
      "title": "Various exponential transforms",
      "problem": "$$\n\\mathcal{L}\\{e^{3t}\\} &= \\frac{1}{s-3}, \\quad s > 3 \\\\[0.5em]\n\\mathcal{L}\\{e^{-2t}\\} &= \\frac{1}{s+2}, \\quad s > -2 \\\\[0.5em]\n\\mathcal{L}\\{e^{-t/2}\\} &= \\frac{1}{s + 1/2} = \\frac{2}{2s+1}, \\quad s > -\\frac{1}{2}\n$$",
      "solution": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Trigonometric Functions"
    },
    {
      "type": "theorem",
      "id": "theorem-6.3",
      "number": "6.3",
      "title": "Transforms of Sine and Cosine",
      "content": "For $s > 0$ and real $b$,\n\\[\n\\mathcal{L}\\{\\sin(bt)\\} = \\frac{b}{s^2 + b^2} \\qquad\\text{and}\\qquad\n\\mathcal{L}\\{\\cos(bt)\\} = \\frac{s}{s^2 + b^2}\n\\]",
      "label": "Theorem"
    },
    {
      "type": "proof",
      "content": "We compute both transforms using integration by parts twice. Let \n$I_c = \\mathcal{L}\\{\\cos(bt)\\}$ and $I_s = \\mathcal{L}\\{\\sin(bt)\\}$.\n\nFor $I_c$, integrate by parts with $u = \\cos(bt)$, $dv = e^{-st}\\,dt$:\n$$\nI_c &= \\int_0^{\\infty} e^{-st}\\cos(bt)\\,dt \\\\\n&= \\left[-\\frac{e^{-st}}{s}\\cos(bt)\\right]_0^{\\infty} - \\frac{b}{s}\\int_0^{\\infty} e^{-st}\\sin(bt)\\,dt \\\\\n&= \\frac{1}{s} - \\frac{b}{s}I_s\n$$\n\nFor $I_s$, similarly:\n$$\nI_s &= \\int_0^{\\infty} e^{-st}\\sin(bt)\\,dt \\\\\n&= \\left[-\\frac{e^{-st}}{s}\\sin(bt)\\right]_0^{\\infty} + \\frac{b}{s}\\int_0^{\\infty} e^{-st}\\cos(bt)\\,dt \\\\\n&= 0 + \\frac{b}{s}I_c = \\frac{b}{s}I_c\n$$\n\nNow we have a system of equations:\n\\[\nI_c = \\frac{1}{s} - \\frac{b}{s}I_s \\qquad\\text{and}\\qquad I_s = \\frac{b}{s}I_c\n\\]\n\nSubstituting the second into the first:\n\\[\nI_c = \\frac{1}{s} - \\frac{b}{s} \\cdot \\frac{b}{s}I_c = \\frac{1}{s} - \\frac{b^2}{s^2}I_c\n\\]\n\\[\nI_c\\left(1 + \\frac{b^2}{s^2}\\right) = \\frac{1}{s} \\implies I_c = \\frac{s}{s^2 + b^2}\n\\]\n\nAnd therefore:\n\\[\nI_s = \\frac{b}{s}I_c = \\frac{b}{s} \\cdot \\frac{s}{s^2 + b^2} = \\frac{b}{s^2 + b^2} \\qedhere\n\\]"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "id": "example-6.4",
      "number": "6.4",
      "title": "Specific trigonometric transforms",
      "problem": "$$\n\\mathcal{L}\\{\\sin(2t)\\} &= \\frac{2}{s^2 + 4} \\\\[0.5em]\n\\mathcal{L}\\{\\cos(3t)\\} &= \\frac{s}{s^2 + 9} \\\\[0.5em]\n\\mathcal{L}\\{\\sin(t/2)\\} &= \\frac{1/2}{s^2 + 1/4} = \\frac{2}{4s^2 + 1}\n$$",
      "solution": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "id": "example-6.5",
      "number": "6.5",
      "title": "A linear combination",
      "problem": "Find $\\mathcal{L}\\{2\\cos(4t) - 3\\sin(4t)\\}$.\n\n**Solution.**\n$$\n\\mathcal{L}\\{2\\cos(4t) - 3\\sin(4t)\\} &= 2\\mathcal{L}\\{\\cos(4t)\\} - 3\\mathcal{L}\\{\\sin(4t)\\} \\\\\n&= 2 \\cdot \\frac{s}{s^2 + 16} - 3 \\cdot \\frac{4}{s^2 + 16} \\\\\n&= \\frac{2s - 12}{s^2 + 16}\n$$",
      "solution": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Hyperbolic Functions"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Recall that $\\sinh(t) = \\frac{e^t - e^{-t}}{2}$ and $\\cosh(t) = \\frac{e^t + e^{-t}}{2}$."
    },
    {
      "type": "theorem",
      "id": "theorem-6.4",
      "number": "6.4",
      "title": "Transforms of Hyperbolic Functions",
      "content": "For $s > |b|$,\n\\[\n\\mathcal{L}\\{\\sinh(bt)\\} = \\frac{b}{s^2 - b^2} \\qquad\\text{and}\\qquad\n\\mathcal{L}\\{\\cosh(bt)\\} = \\frac{s}{s^2 - b^2}\n\\]",
      "label": "Theorem"
    },
    {
      "type": "proof",
      "content": "Using the definitions and linearity:\n$$\n\\mathcal{L}\\{\\sinh(bt)\\} &= \\mathcal{L}\\left\\{\\frac{e^{bt} - e^{-bt}}{2}\\right\\} \\\\\n&= \\frac{1}{2}\\left(\\frac{1}{s-b} - \\frac{1}{s+b}\\right) \\\\\n&= \\frac{1}{2} \\cdot \\frac{(s+b) - (s-b)}{(s-b)(s+b)} \\\\\n&= \\frac{1}{2} \\cdot \\frac{2b}{s^2 - b^2} = \\frac{b}{s^2 - b^2}\n$$\n\nSimilarly for $\\cosh(bt)$:\n$$\n\\mathcal{L}\\{\\cosh(bt)\\} &= \\frac{1}{2}\\left(\\frac{1}{s-b} + \\frac{1}{s+b}\\right) \\\\\n&= \\frac{1}{2} \\cdot \\frac{2s}{s^2 - b^2} = \\frac{s}{s^2 - b^2} \\qedhere\n$$"
    },
    {
      "type": "remark",
      "id": "remark-6.2",
      "number": null,
      "title": "",
      "content": "Notice the similarity between the transforms of trigonometric and hyperbolic \nfunctions. The difference $s^2 + b^2$ versus $s^2 - b^2$ reflects the \nrelationship $\\sinh(bt) = -i\\sin(ibt)$ and $\\cosh(bt) = \\cos(ibt)$ from \ncomplex analysis."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Summary Table"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The following table collects the basic transforms derived in this section:"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "headers": [
        "$f(t)$",
        "$F(s) = \\mathcal{L}\\{f(t)\\}$"
      ],
      "rows": [
        [
          "$1$",
          "$\\displaystyle\\frac{1}{s}$, $s > 0$"
        ],
        [
          "$t^n$ $(n = 0, 1, 2, \\ldots)$",
          "$\\displaystyle\\frac{n!}{s^{n+1}}$, $s > 0$"
        ],
        [
          "$e^{at}$",
          "$\\displaystyle\\frac{1}{s-a}$, $s > a$"
        ],
        [
          "$\\sin(bt)$",
          "$\\displaystyle\\frac{b}{s^2 + b^2}$, $s > 0$"
        ],
        [
          "$\\cos(bt)$",
          "$\\displaystyle\\frac{s}{s^2 + b^2}$, $s > 0$"
        ],
        [
          "$\\sinh(bt)$",
          "$\\displaystyle\\frac{b}{s^2 - b^2}$, $s > |b|$"
        ],
        [
          "$\\cosh(bt)$",
          "$\\displaystyle\\frac{s}{s^2 - b^2}$, $s > |b|$"
        ]
      ],
      "alignment": [
        "left",
        "left"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "id": "example-6.6",
      "number": "6.6",
      "title": "A comprehensive example",
      "problem": "Find $\\mathcal{L}\\{f(t)\\}$ where $f(t) = t^3 - 2e^{-t} + 4\\cos(5t)$.\n\n**Solution.** By linearity:\n$$\n\\mathcal{L}\\{f(t)\\} &= \\mathcal{L}\\{t^3\\} - 2\\mathcal{L}\\{e^{-t}\\} + 4\\mathcal{L}\\{\\cos(5t)\\} \\\\\n&= \\frac{6}{s^4} - \\frac{2}{s+1} + \\frac{4s}{s^2 + 25}\n$$",
      "solution": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "id": "example-6.7",
      "number": "6.7",
      "title": "Expanding before transforming",
      "problem": "Find $\\mathcal{L}\\{(t + 1)^3\\}$.\n\n**Solution.** First expand:\n\\[\n(t+1)^3 = t^3 + 3t^2 + 3t + 1\n\\]\nThen:\n$$\n\\mathcal{L}\\{(t+1)^3\\} &= \\mathcal{L}\\{t^3\\} + 3\\mathcal{L}\\{t^2\\} + 3\\mathcal{L}\\{t\\} + \\mathcal{L}\\{1\\} \\\\\n&= \\frac{6}{s^4} + \\frac{6}{s^3} + \\frac{3}{s^2} + \\frac{1}{s}\n$$",
      "solution": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "id": "example-6.8",
      "number": "6.8",
      "title": "Using trigonometric identities",
      "problem": "Find $\\mathcal{L}\\{\\sin^2(t)\\}$.\n\n**Solution.** Use the identity $\\sin^2(t) = \\frac{1 - \\cos(2t)}{2}$:\n$$\n\\mathcal{L}\\{\\sin^2(t)\\} &= \\frac{1}{2}\\mathcal{L}\\{1\\} - \\frac{1}{2}\\mathcal{L}\\{\\cos(2t)\\} \\\\\n&= \\frac{1}{2} \\cdot \\frac{1}{s} - \\frac{1}{2} \\cdot \\frac{s}{s^2 + 4} \\\\\n&= \\frac{1}{2s} - \\frac{s}{2(s^2 + 4)} \\\\\n&= \\frac{s^2 + 4 - s^2}{2s(s^2 + 4)} = \\frac{2}{s(s^2 + 4)}\n$$",
      "solution": ""
    }
  ]
}